Program: Great Lives
Title: Laura Serrant on Audre Lorde
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b09zxl90
Last Broadcast Date: Tue 24 Apr 2018
Professor Laura Serrant of Sheffield Hallam University, named as one of the most inspirational figures in healthcare, chooses the life of the black, gay poet and activist Audre Lorde who still inspires the women's movement today. She tells Matthew Parris why Audre has meant so much to her both personally and professionally in her work in nursing. Professor Akwugo Emejulu of Warwick University is the studio expert. Producer: Maggie Ayre. Show less